HEADWORD: Heterocercal
<hw>Het`er*o*cer"cal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hetero-</ets> + Gr. <?/ tail.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Having the vertebral column evidently continued into the upper lobe
of the tail, which is usually longer than the lower one, as in
sharks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

